rComments: One of the best profs at U of T. Respects his students. Very accommodating and helpful. Vey knowledgeable about pol-sci and many other things.  A great person and a great teacher.
Great Proff you will know once you take his courses.

AMAZING professor. use of personal anecdotes supplements the content of the course - Canadian politics. goes through concepts rather thoroughly and makes sure the point has been reinforced before proceeding. lectures build off one another. would have enjoyed more scholarly articles
great prof. articulates points clearly and is an awesome orator. It was a pleasure to attend his lecture every morning. Is a valuable asset to the the UofT Political Science Department
Chris was one of the best TAs I have ever had.  He is such a nice person, interested in helping you out and has the cutest stories about his daughter.

Outstanding TA with the potential to be a truly amazing professor down the road.  He makes Canadian politics interesting with little anecdotes and his whacky sense of humour...and that ain't easy to do.  A definite asset to U of T!
Chris is an excellent lecturer, and an even better TA. Hopefully U of T offers him a position as a professor. This is one man they do not want to lose.
